And to expand a little (if I may):

The method of protest these players have chosen does not speak to what they are protesting, like you said.  The National Anthem is the NATIONAL Anthem.  It represents our nation as a whole, not one aspect that may be broken, corrupt, failing it citizens.  The freedoms the Anthem represents INCLUDES your right to a peaceful protest.  So WHY choose that time to show your discontent?  It makes no sense. 

&amp;#x200B;

It is not the Police Anthem.  It is not the Anthem of unfair treatment.  To me, (and I may be alone) that particular song is very dear and it represents all of the pain, deaths and triumphs of not only those who fought for the US but also those that were brave enough to risk life and limb to get here in the first place.   

&amp;#x200B;

Our system is not perfect and it does fail, sometimes a lot.  If I were protesting a particular injustice I would like to think the avenue I choose to do it would bring attention to the actual injustice.
